%S A394932 6,106,966,1484,3528,8176,18592
%N A394932 Number of point sets with a unique stable state in the 3 X n neighborhood grid.
%H A394932 Alex McDonough, Ulrich Reitebuch, and Martin Skrodzki, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.dam.2025.03.028">Combinatorial and asymptotic results on the neighborhood grid</a>, Discrete Applied Mathematics, Volume 372, 2025, 48-64. <a href="https://ms-math-computer.science/preprint/2025_MRS_NeigborhoodGrid.pdf">Link to a preprint</a>.
%e A394932 For n=1, the a(1)=6 solutions are given by {(1,s(1)),(2,s(2)), (3,s(3))}, where s is one of the a(1)=6 permutations of the numbers {1,2,3}.
%Y A394932 Cf. A000142 (1 X n grid), A394931 (2 X n grid).
